 As you can see, the <a> element has four attributes that TubePress needs to work with: class, href, rel, and target.
 You may add to these attributes - e.g. add a class name - but do not remove any of the attributes
 as doing so will likely break playback.

 @var $mediaItem tubepress_app_api_media_MediaItem
#}
<a class="tubepress-cursor-pointer js-tubepress-invoker js-tubepress-itemid-{{ mediaItem.id }}"

    {% if mediaItem.hasAttribute('invokingAnchorUrl') %}
        href="{{ mediaItem.getAttribute('invokingAnchorUrl') }}"
    {% endif %}

    {% if mediaItem.hasAttribute('invokingAnchorRel') %}
        rel="{{ mediaItem.getAttribute('invokingAnchorRel') }}"
    {% endif %}

    {% if mediaItem.hasAttribute('invokingAnchorTarget') %}
        target="{{ mediaItem.getAttribute('invokingAnchorTarget') }}"
    {% endif %}>